    • Class org.openwms.core.uaa.User extends org.ameba.integration.jpa.ApplicationEntity implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • username

          String username
          Unique identifier of this User (not nullable).

        • extern

          boolean extern
          true if the User is authenticated by an external system, otherwise false.

        • lastPasswordChange

          Date lastPasswordChange
          Date of the last password change.

        • locked

          boolean locked
          true if this User is locked and has not the permission to login anymore. This field is set by the backend application, e.g. when the expirationDate of the account has expired.

        • password

          String password
          The User's current password (only kept transient).

        • persistedPassword

          String persistedPassword
          The User's current password.

        • enabled

          boolean enabled
          true if the User is enabled. This field can be managed by the UI application to lock an User manually.

        • expirationDate

          Date expirationDate
          Date when the account expires. After account expiration, the User cannot login anymore.

        • fullname

          String fullname
          The User's fullname. Doesn't have to be unique.

        • primaryEmailAddress

          Email primaryEmailAddress

        • emailAddresses

          Set<E> emailAddresses

        • userDetails

          UserDetails userDetails
          More detail information of the User.

        • roles

          List<E> roles
          List of Roles assigned to the User. In a JPA context eager loaded.
          See Also:
          FetchType.EAGER

        • passwords

          List<E> passwords
          Password history of the User.
